wiki.summary: On "If We Being Rëal", Yeat touches on themes of isolation, detachment, and a sense of superiority. The lyrics explore feelings of emptiness, disconnection from others, and a desire for control. There’s a sense of defiance and a refusal to conform to societal norms, with an emphasis on self-preservation and maintaining personal boundaries. The instrumental of the song has mysterious, futuristic elements, almost giving it a dreamy ethereal touch. Read more on Last.fm.
